      "span_text": "In previous research, Huntley and Redalje cultivated Haematococcus pluvialis to produce oil and astaxanthin (used in salmon feed) using a twostage system. As a result, the annual average microbial oil production rate was more than 10 toe ha-1 per annum with a maximum rate of 24 toe ha-1 per annum [CITATION_1] ."
